  ('63d5fdbb-076a-5518-ad92-991e250b80e6', 'GJ_RF_001', 'IND_GJ_D01', 'GJ_ROLE001_DR01', 'Diamond Planner operates in Rough diamond planning and yield control within the Gems & Jewellery industry. The role handles rough parcel and planned diamond using planning sheet; yield estimate; stone map. Day to day, the role plan sawing, mark yield, flag inclusions; it prepares traceable evidence, checks exceptions and routes unresolved items to the named authority. The role may prepare rough-diamond parcel planning inputs including assorting notes, size grouping, yield estimate, sawing or cutting-plan support, risk flags and planning handoff artifacts for review., but cannot independently approve rough valuation, final sawing plan, buyer-grade commitment, parcel release, or commercial acceptance decision.. Escalation is required when escalate when parcel identity is unclear, expected yield differs materially from plan, inclusion or breakage risk changes the cutting approach, valuation assumptions conflict, or buyer approval is needed.. Output proof includes Rough parcel planning sheet and buyer-ready sawing-plan handoff note;Yield estimate sheet and sawing-plan review note.', 'R', 'I', 'C', 'RIC', 'Diamond Planner is mapped to RIC because the role combines hands-on production, tools, materials, inspection, physical process control and artifact discipline; analysis, evidence comparison, anomaly detection, technical reasoning and controlled judgement; and structured records, traceability, compliance, documentation, scheduling and accuracy-focused control while producing controlled workplace evidence such as planning sheet; yield estimate; stone map.', 'Match parcel ID, declared weight, buyer instruction and planning sheet reference before opening the planning entry. | Compare inclusion position, visible risk and expected yield with the proposed shape target and planning tolerance. | Enter sawing-risk note, recommended handoff route and dated planner remark in the planning shee