  ('517a7772-4fca-5577-8c99-58e98a2a378e', 'GJ_RF_004', 'IND_GJ_D04', 'GJ_ROLE004_DR01', 'LGD Growth Technician operates in LGD growth and batch traceability within the Gems & Jewellery industry. The role handles growth batch and LGD rough using growth log; batch exception note. Day to day, the role monitor batch conditions and log growth traceability; it prepares traceable evidence, checks exceptions and routes unresolved items to the named authority. The role may maintain lgd growth batch records, monitor assigned process parameters, record equipment readings, flag deviations and prepare batch handoff notes for screening and disclosure review., but cannot independently certify origin, alter growth records, suppress process deviations, approve undisclosed lgd release, or make final hpht/cvd disclosure decisions.. Escalation is required when escalate when batch identity is uncertain, growth parameters move outside tolerance, equipment alarms occur, traceability records are incomplete, or origin/disclosure evidence conflicts.. Output proof includes LGD batch record and traceability handoff note;Equipment parameter sheet and exception log.', 'I', 'C', 'R', 'ICR', 'LGD Growth Technician is mapped to ICR because the role combines analysis, evidence comparison, anomaly detection, technical reasoning and controlled judgement; structured records, traceability, compliance, documentation, scheduling and accuracy-focused control; and hands-on production, tools, materials, inspection, physical process control and artifact discipline while producing controlled workplace evidence such as growth log; batch exception note.', 'Create or update the batch record with batch ID, equipment reference, seed reference and process stage. | Compare the run-sheet stage entry with the batch traceability chain before allowing the next processing step. | Enter abnormal event, dated comment and next handoff status in the batch record; hold the batch and route the exception to LGD Production Manag