cial": 3.0, "lifestyle": 5.0, "creativity": 3.0, "leadership": 3.0}'::jsonb, '{"areas": ["Logical Reasoning", "Pattern Recognition", "Data Interpretation"], "rationale": "Ward Secretary depends most on logical reasoning; pattern recognition; data interpretation because the work involves matching identifiers, checking source documents, updating systems, recognising exception cues and preparing traceable handoff evidence. Lower readiness should trigger bridge practice rather than automatic rejection unless the role is safety, licence or authority gated."}'::jsonb, '{"traits": ["Agreeableness", "Conscientiousness", "Emotional Stability"], "rationale": "Ward Secretary benefits from agreeableness; conscientiousness; emotional stability because the role requires accurate evidence handling, supervised communication, privacy discipline and calm exception escalation. These traits should adjust confidence and coaching focus, not act as a hard exclusion rule."}'::jsonb, '{"values": ["Impact", "Lifestyle Fit", "Security"], "rationale": "Ward Secretary aligns best with learners who value impact; lifestyle fit; security because the environment involves structured service support, reliable documentation, patient-facing or internal coordination and visible evidence of completed work. Work values should prioritise role options, not prove technical ability."}'::jsonb, 'Preferred', 'B.Pharm/D.Pharm where regulated; Life Sciences; Healthcare Operations; Any degree for non-dispensing documentation support', true),
